cs.GT, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.EC 

The paper deals with game theoretic analysis of keyword auctions, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of simulations and analysis of auction mechanisms also suggests a possible fit under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the study of profit as a function of auction mechanism falls under the category of computational economics (cs.EC).
